text: The Ventura County Star (Marked online as VC Star) is a daily newspaper that comes out in Camarillo, California. It gives news for the whole Ventura County area. Gannett, which is the biggest company that publishes newspapers in the United States, owns it. The Ventura County Star was created after several other daily newspapers in Ventura County combined throughout the 20th century.Saillant, Kay - Camarillo Daily News to Close in December : Media: The 67-year-old publication will be replaced with a zoned version of the Ventura County Star-Free Press.
